Male genitalia (
Fig. 10
): Tegumen subrectangular, obtuse on posterior margin. Socius approximately 0.33 length of tegumen, with sparse short setae. Valva with basal excavation approximately 0.25 length of valva; costa obtusely produced at about basal 0.33; sacculus approximately 0.33 length of valva, right angled ventroapically; neck distinct, approximately half maximum width of cucullus; cucullus elongate, approximately 2 times length of sacculus, elliptically expanded and hairy distally, ventral margin roundly produced and with a cluster of dense spines at about basal 0.33, concave at about middle, with a large spine set at about distal 0.33. Phallus approximately half length of valva; cornuti consisting of numerous needlelike spines.

Female genitalia (
Fig. 14
): Sternite VII with large widely divided sclerites extending along lateral side of ostium bursae to posterior 0.33, connected anteriorly below ostium bursae, rounded on posterior margin, with narrow spinulose hump on anterior margin at each side of ostium bursae. Ostium bursae situated in middle near anterior margin of sternite VII. Antrum approximately 0.66 length of ductus bursae; colliculum being a broad ring at distal 0.25 of ductus bursae; ductus bursae nearly equal length to corpus bursae. Corpus bursae ovate; two signa bladeshaped, with rounded basal plate; appendix bursae and corpus bursae equal in size; ductus seminalis originating from base of appendix bursae. Sternite VI with posterior margin sclerotized medially.
